ROCKET AND ROLL got bumped at the start by TOP ENVOY, chased three then two wide coming under coaxing at the five-sixteenths, swung two to three wide into upper stretch, took over command at the three-sixteenths, dug in under threat and was bumped by SELL SOMETHING and in turn bumped LEFTEMBEHIND just inside the eighth pole when being overhauled by the top one, then weakened in the late stages. NOBLE HUNTSMAN chased two to three wide coming under coaxing at the five-sixteenths, angled six to seven wide into upper stretch and made no impact. SHINSUN chased along the inside, tipped two to three wide through the far turn coming under coaxing at the five-sixteenths, went eight wide into upper stretch and made no impact. LT. MITCHELL led early on inside, got headed for the front five furlongs from home, came under coaxing at the five-sixteenths briefly, spun just off the inside into upper stretch, tired and was eased home to the finish, then was reported to have bled. There was a Stewards' Inquiry into the stretch run as well as a Jockey's Objection by the rider of ROCKET AND ROLL alleging interference against BE OF COURAGE. After review, it was deemed that BE OF COURAGE had caused interference to ROCKET AND ROLL and therefore BE OF COURAGE was disqualified and placed fourth before the result was declared official.
